I like to not put my beer in the refrigerator, but leave it outside on the balcony or the windowsill. It feels more natural this way, otherwise it's never just the *right* temperature. Also this way it corresponds to nature outside. If there's a rainstorm it's colder, evenings...

it's chillier than in mornings etc. Helps you get a feel of the physical world. In summer days beer is best put in the basement, and if you lack one, then this is the only time the refrigerator comes in handy. I suggest you try this method, makes drinking a tad more interesting.
